{"questionId": "b310cd51-4e49-46d2-99c8-70a10c0d83f9_15", "correctAnswer": "C", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Apply vertex form", "content": "Since we know the vertex is $(1, 6)$, use the vertex form directly. Substituting $h = 1$ and $k = 6$:<br/>$$f(x) = a(x - 1)^2 + 6$$", "formula": "$$f(x) = a(x - h)^2 + k$$"}, {"title": "Find the leading coefficient", "content": "Use the point $(2, 40)$ to determine $a$:<br/>$$40 = a(2 - 1)^2 + 6$$<br/>$$40 = a + 6$$<br/>$$a = 34$$"}, {"title": "Calculate the difference", "content": "Evaluate $f(-2)$ and $f(0)$ using $f(x) = 34(x - 1)^2 + 6$:<br/><br/>For $f(-2)$:<br/>$$f(-2) = 34(-2 - 1)^2 + 6 = 34(9) + 6 = 306 + 6 = 312$$<br/>For $f(0)$:<br/>$$f(0) = 34(0 - 1)^2 + 6 = 34(1) + 6 = 40$$<br/>Therefore:<br/>$$f(-2) - f(0) = 312 - 40 = 272$$<br/>That matches choice C — <strong>C</strong> is correct."}]}